               <p>THOMAS CHANDLER. I lost a coat and waistcoat on the 13th of March, from a counting-house in <placeName id="t18300415-362-crimeloc1960">Little Tower-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-362-crimeloc1960" type="placeName" value="Little Tower-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-362-crimeloc1960" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-362-off1958 t18300415-362-crimeloc1960"></join>, belonging to my employer - I was attracted by the shutting of the counting-house door, and on looking through a window I saw the prisoner with the coat and waistcoat on his arm - I ran out, he dropped them, and hesitated which way he should go; he turned to the left; I went, and took him, when he had ran about fifty yards.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183004150152"></xptr>Prisoner's Defence. I was very ill, and had been in the hospital - I had my doctor's bill to pay.</p>
